{"content_excerpt":"-- Mustard harness store ‚Äî SQLite schema for `SqliteEventStore`.\n-- Idempotent: every CREATE uses IF NOT EXISTS. Safe to run on every open().\n--\n-- ============================================================================\n-- W5 (2026-05-24-mustard-unification) ‚Äî lean schema redesign.\n--\n-- The hot-path event log moved to per-spec NDJSON files\n-- (`.claude/spec/{name}/events/*.ndjson`) ‚Äî see\n-- `apps/rt/src/run/event_writer_ndjson.rs`. Run-cost telemetry lives in the\n-- sibling `telemetry.db` (`run_usage`, `usage_totals`). What stays in\n-- `mustard.db` is the **lifecycle index** + the long-lived domain tables.\n--\n-- Dropped vs the v9 schema (no migration data carry ‚Äî per dev-phase guidance):\n--\n--   * `events` + `events_fts`          ‚Üí replaced by NDJSON per-spec files\n--   * `knowledge` + `knowledge_fts`    ‚Üí consolidated into `knowledge_patterns`\n--   * `metrics_projection`             ‚Üí duplicated `telemetry.db.run_usage`\n--   * `api_cost_frames`                ‚Üí consolidated into `telemetry.db.run_usage`\n--\n-- Kept:\n--\n--   * `pipeline_events`        ‚Äî low-volume lifecycle index (status/phase/task)\n--   * `sessions`               ‚Äî session registry (Claude Code session ids)\n--   * `pipeline_amend_window`  ‚Äî session-bound amendment windows\n--   * `specs`                  ‚Äî denormalized per-spec cache for fast lists\n--   * `savings_records`        ‚Äî one row per Mustard intervention (writer hot)\n--   * `context_cost_frames`    ‚Äî one row per agent dispatch (writer hot)\n--   * `knowledge_patterns`     ‚Äî extracted patterns (FTS5 mirror)\n--   * `memory_decisions`       ‚Äî architectural decisions journal (FTS5 mirror)\n--   * `memory_lessons`         ‚Äî lessons learned journal (FTS5 mirror)\n--   * `agent_memory`           ‚Äî agent self-memory (W8 owns logic, DDL here)\n--   * `memory_feedback`        ‚Äî feedback signals on agent_memory rows\n--\n-- ## Index audit\n--\n-- Each consumer query was traced through `EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN`-style review.\n-- The final index list (matches each `CREATE INDEX` below):\n--\n--   pipeline_events:\n--     idx_pipeline_events_spec          ‚Äî list-by-spec scans\n--     idx_pipeline_events_kind          ‚Äî by-kind probes\n--     idx_pipeline_events_spec_kind     ‚Äî list-by-spec-and-kind (hot)\n--     idx_pipeline_events_session_kind  ‚Äî `last_pipeline_scope_for_session`\n--     idx_pipeline_events_parent        ‚Äî task-child recursion\n--     idx_pipeline_events_ts            ‚Äî chronological sort\n--\n--   sessions:\n--     idx_sessions_last_activity        ‚Äî recent-first listing\n--     idx_sessions_status               ‚Äî filter by status\n--\n--   pipeline_amend_window:\n--     PK(spec_id, session_id)           ‚Äî single-key lookup\n--     idx_pipeline_amend_window_session_status\n--\n--   knowledge_patterns:\n--     UNIQUE(pattern)                   ‚Äî dedupe writes\n--     idx_knowledge_patterns_pattern    ‚Äî exact-match lookup\n--     idx_knowledge_patterns_last_seen  ‚Äî recent-first\n--     idx_knowledge_patterns_confidence_last_seen ‚Äî SessionStart inject rank\n--     idx_knowledge_patterns_spec       ‚Äî per-spec scope (W5/W8)\n--\n--   memory_decisions / memory_lessons:\n--     idx_memory_{decisions,lessons}_at         ‚Äî recent-first\n--     idx_memory_{decisions,lessons}_spec       ‚Äî per-spec scope (W5/W8)\n--     idx_memory_{decisions,lessons}_status     ‚Äî active-only filters\n--\n--   agent_memory:\n--     idx_agent_memory_spec\n--     idx_agent_memory_status_confidence ‚Äî active+top-confidence inject rank\n--     idx_agent_memory_session\n--\n--   memory_feedback:\n--     idx_memory_feedback_memory_id\n--     idx_memory_feedback_kind\n--\n-- ============================================================================\n\n-- pipeline_events: low-volume lifecycle events the dashboard reads by spec.\n-- `kind` is the canonical event name (`pipeline.scope`, `pipeline.status`,\n-- `pipeline.phase`, `pipeline.wave.complete`, `pipeline.wave.failed`,\n-- `pipeline.task.dispatch`, `pipeline.task.complete`, `pipeline.complete`,\n-- and the `pipeline.economy.*` family). Tool / agent / ... [truncated, 11823 bytes more]","file_path":"C:\\Atiz\\mustard\\packages\\core\\src\\store\\sqlite_schema.sql","tool":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RWYmimCcrhF3AuMSHeUyL9"}